    "title": "Prayer of the Guest Chaplain of the U.S. Senate: Rabbi Theodore Lewis on 18 February 1963",
    "author": "Theodore Lewis",
    "coauthors": [
        {
            "name": "Theodore Lewis",
            "bio": "Theodore Lewis (1915-2010), born in Dublin, Ireland, led Congregation Jeshuat Israel (Touro Synagogue) in Newport, Rhode Island for 36 years, beginning in 1949. He studied in the Mir Yeshiva in Poland from from 1935 to 1939. On 30 June 1959, he appeared on the television program, <em>To Tell the Truth</em>. He published two works: <em>Sermons at Touro Synagogue</em> (1980) and a companion volume, <em>Bar Mitzvah Sermons at Touro Synagogue</em> (1989).",
